Stage 7: Representatives + Anchors
ParameterValueTypeWhy this value_REP_HAC_THRESHOLD0.5FIXEDHAC cut for sub-clustering. 0.5 = 50% cosine distance. Tested: 0.3 over-splits, 0.7 under-splits._ANCHOR_IC_MIN4.0FIXEDIC=4 ≈ 2% of hierarchy. Below: too broad ("Clinical finding" routes everywhere)._ANCHOR_BFS_DEPTH4FIXED4 hops UP from rep → mid-level ancestors for routing._ANCHOR_IC_MAX_BROAD3.0FIXEDAbsolute safety floor. Reject anchors below IC=3.0.
Selection: per topic, group by semantic category, sub-cluster via HAC, pick one rep per sub-cluster. Preference: parent-within-set → embedding medoid → highest IC.
Query: 2 reps (one per subtopic). Document: 67 reps.
Anchors (documents only): routing shortcuts stored with the chunk.

Stage 8: Centroids
L2-normalized mean of member CUI embeddings (3072-dim). Same formula for queries and documents.
Query: 1 centroid. Document: 60 centroids. These are what Pass 1 compares. Opus 4.6Extended
